res by  they had a warehouse on west henrietta road by the end of  they had about  stores in new york from this warehouse drivers would load the trucks and deliver to all the  stores throughout new york afterwards a more aggressive expansion program was instituted when the company began to make a number of large acquisitions by the mids there were  stores which generated  million in sales annually most of those locations were located in upstate new york expansionedit headquarters in rochester new york in  the companys founder charles j august sold his controlling interest in monro muffler and brake to a new york citybased investors group headed by donald glickman and peter j solomon august remained on the companys board of directors until  in  monro muffler made its initial public offering monros stock began trading on nasdaq under the symbol mnro under the leadership of robert g gross who joined the company in  as president and ceo and currently serves as executive chairman monro aggressively expanded outside of its traditional base in upstate new york in september  the company successfully purchased all  speedy muffler king locations within the united states from speedy muffler king inc of toronto canada in  monro purchased the  stores and  kiosks of mr tire a baltimore maryland chain which trademarked “on the rim and out the door” pricing later that year monro bought five rice tire locations and rebranded them as mr tire auto service centers monro now operates  mr tire outlets in  monro obtained  procare shops from bankruptcy converting  to monro muffler brake  service centers and  to mr tire outlets in fiscal  the company purchased the  autotire stores in missouri and illinois its first venture into the midwest and the  tire warehouse central stores in massachusetts rhode island vermont and new hampshire fiscal  began with the acquisition of import export tire co five retail tire and auto repair stores in the pittsburgh pennsylvania metro region and courthouse tire three tire and undercar care facilities in the fredericksburg virginia area whos sales substantially declined after the acquisition in fiscal  the company acquired eight local auto service and retail groups including tire barn warehouse  stores in indiana illinois and tennessee and ken towerys tire  autocare  stores in kentucky and indiana two chains that monro continues to manage under the local brand names this is also true of currys auto service in virginia and maryland a store acquisition in fiscal  that year the company also purchased four ss firestone stores in kentucky and six carl king tire stores in delaware and maryland monro entered three new states with major acquisitions in  michigan  lentz usakan rock tire  stores florida  the tire choice  total car care  stores gold coast tire  auto centers  stores and martino tire  stores and georgia  wood  fullerton  stores the company operates its florida stores under the tire choice brand in fiscal  the company purchased the carx trade name and franchise rights to  locations in illinois wisconsin iowa minnesota and texas since  monro has made more than  acquisitions totaling more than  stores and producing revenue of  million under monros current ceo john van heel the company continues to pursue a growth strategy of increased market share through incremental store sales lowcost acquisitions and strategic new store openings monro serviced  million vehicles in  and posted record sales of  million record net income of  million and earnings of  per share the company operates under several regional brands most acquired in the past  years including monro muffler brake  service mr tire auto service centers tread quarters discount tire auto service centers autotire car care centers ken towerys tire  autocare currys auto service the tire choice  total car care tire warehouse tires for less and tire barn warehouse referencesedit  a b c d e f g monro muffler brake inc  form k for the fiscal year ended march   washington 